<font color="#FF0000">ERNEST, BE PROUD!</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26 23:02:27 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Ernest,<br><br>
Consider Tom's and Mike's words carefully. They speak a truth drawn from experience. <br><br>
No burden is imposed upon us by those who fell. Each of us has a place in the larger scheme of things. Our place is here and now. In ways we are very much with our fallen buddies, and we honor them still with our memories.<br><br>
I was in Vietnam in 69/70. Artillery was my game. It was no picnic. It was then a war of doing everything in our power to save our buddies from harms way. We all did our part, and we did it well.<br><br>
...and so did you.<br><br>
Be proud. 
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


